
xgrid(2)                       Scilab Function                       xgrid(2)
NAME
  xgrid - add a grid on a 2D plot

CALLING SEQUENCE
  xgrid([style])

PARAMETERS

  style  : integer

DESCRIPTION
  xgrid adds a grid on a 2D plot. style is the dash id or the color id to use
  for the grid plotting. Use xset() for the meaning of id.

EXAMPLE
  x=[0:0.1:2*%pi]';
  plot2d(sin(x))
  xgrid(2)

SEE ALSO
  xset, plot2d

